<doc id="313224" wikidata="Q7431187" url="?curid=313224" title="Scheppau">
<text>Scheppau is a river of Lower Saxony, Germany, approximately long. The Scheppau originates on the slope of the Elm hills and is a left tributary of the Schunter. It flows west and north of Königslutter and joins the Schunter in Glentorf, between Königslutter and Wolfsburg.

